Variables¶

A Python variable is a symbolic name that refers to a specific memory address where the value is stored.

In [1]:
x = 5

Things to remember:

  • x is name of the variable.
  • = is the assignment operator used to assign values to variables.
  • 5 is the value that x refers to.

When you assign a variable¶

When you re-assign a variable¶

Rules for naming variables¶

  • Variable names may only contain letters, digits, and/or the underscore character.
  • Variable name cannot start with a digit.
  • Variable name cannot be a keyword in Python.
